comments.body: is there reason to keep this around?

I think so. This actually tests being able to pass in an array of objects rather than just an array of numbers, so it's slightly different.

I didn't want to uncomment it right now, but I could see how it could be useful to remind us of other test-cases once we get around to writing more later on.

I'm less concerned about this commented-out test, and more concerned with the tests below it (lines 16-26), which appear to be a copy of the first uncommented test-case (lines 3-9) except with the addition of the curried test-case. I had removed other duplicate tests for other functions, so I'm not 100% sure why I left that one behind.

Still, no harm no foul. We can clean them up further later-on.
